[normal]case of weak contract managemen
[normal]t.  Our message has always been to treat fraud as fraud.  That is perhaps changing a little, but there is still that within the system.
[normal]Q412 [bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]Mark [bold]Pawsey[bold]:[bold] When that fraud occurs, that causes reputational damage to the body involved.  The other two types of fraud that the Audit Commission identified were: the dangers of 
[normal]supplier 
[normal]insolvency, where too onerous a contract may push the supplier out of business, and service failure.  All of that damages the reputation of the procuring body, in this case the local council.  We have heard quite extensively from Mr Bryce about fraud, but, on those other two risks, are councils sufficiently adept at managing risk, picking up the point made by Mrs
[normal]&#xa0;
