[normal]Q414 [bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]David [bold]Heyes[bold]:[bold] Mr Bryce has anticipated the line of questioning I was going to pursue on fraud in the very comprehensive and helpful responses we have had so far.  You briefly mentioned whistleblowers.  Would you say that 
[normal]whistleblowing
[normal] is the main source of identification of fraud? What proportion is it?
[normal]Alan Bryce[bold]: I would not have the specific statistics.
