[normal]other things should be happening to nip the fraud in the bud before we become so dependent on whistleblowers?
[normal]Alan Bryce[bold]: There are other very effective
[normal] techniques
[normal] to identify fraud.  I go back to my earlier response.  Probably the 
[normal]one consideration we really should be 
[normal]giving thought to is around deterrence.  
[normal]There is relatively little
[normal] deterrence from the perspective of fraud currently in the system, by which I mean that to have effective deterrence you must have a
[normal] reasonable capaci
[normal]ty to identify and detect fraud initially;
[normal] and
